_‚ö†Ô∏è Potential issue_ | _üü† Major_

**Limitation: Only the first captured variable is used.**

When the lambda body references multiple external fields, all are added to `args` by the visitor, but only `args[2]` (first captured variable) is used here. Subsequent captured variables are ignored.



If multiple captured variables are supported, consider using a higher-arity function or passing captured vars as an array:

```diff
         if (hasCapturedVars) {
-          // Lambda has captured variables - pass the first captured variable as second arg
-          Object capturedVar = args[2];
+          // Lambda has captured variables - currently only one is supported
+          if (args.length > 4) {
+            throw new UnsupportedOperationException(
+                "Lambdas with multiple captured variables are not yet supported");
+          }
+          Object capturedVar = args[2];
           for (Object candidate : target) {
```

Alternatively, document this as a known limitation if single-capture is intentional for `mvmap`.

